{"word":"insequor","priority":"☆☆☆","meanings":[{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"追跡する、追いかける、後に続く","english_definition":"to follow after, pursue, chase; to come after, succeed.","examples":[{"sentence":"Hostes fugientes insequuntur.","translation":"彼らは逃げる敵を追跡する。"},{"sentence":"Gloria virtutem insequitur.","translation":"名声は美徳の後に続く。"}],"collocations":["insequi hostes (敵を追跡する)","insequi fugientes (逃げる者を追跡する)","insequi cursum (進路をたどる)","tempus insequens (後の時間)"],"synonyms":["persequor","sector","sequor","consequor"],"antonyms":["praecedo","antecedo","fugio"]},{"part_of_speech":"verb","definition":"（比喩的に）追求する、追い求める、目指す","english_definition":"(figuratively) to strive for, aim at, pursue.","examples":[{"sentence":"Honestatem insequi debemus.","translation":"私たちは誠実さを追求すべきだ。"},{"sentence":"Gloriam et divitias insequuntur.","translation":"彼らは名声と富を追い求める。"}],"collocations":["insequi gloriam (名声を追求する)","insequi virtutem (美徳を追求する)","insequi pacem (平和を追求する)"],"synonyms":["appeto","peto","expeto","studere"],"antonyms":["desisto","abstinere"]}],"etymology":{"value":"ラテン語の「in-」（～の中に、～に向かって）+ 「sequor」（従う、後に続く）から構成される。","priority":"★★☆"},"pronunciation":{"ipa":"/inˈse.kʷor/","syllables":"in-se-quor"},"inflection":{"verb_forms":{"present_indicative":["insequor","insequeris","insequitur","insequimur","insequimini","insequuntur"],"imperfect_indicative":["insequebar","insequebaris","insequebatur","insequebamur","insequebamini","insequebantur"],"future_indicative":["insequar","insequeris","insequetur","insequemur","insequemini","insequentur"],"perfect_indicative":["insecutus sum","insecutus es","insecutus est","insecuti sumus","insecuti estis","insecuti sunt"],"pluperfect_indicative":["insecutus eram","insecutus eras","insecutus erat","insecuti eramus","insecuti eratis","insecuti erant"],"future_perfect_indicative":["insecutus ero","insecutus eris","insecutus erit","insecuti erimus","insecuti eritis","insecuti erunt"],"present_subjunctive":["insequar","insequaris","insequatur","insequ